White House Media Wars, NASCAR=E2=80=99s Loyalty Test, Brexit Fashion
---------------------------------------------------------------

Happy Friday and welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon compilat=
ion of Puck=E2=80=99s
best new reporting.

=C2=A0

Today, we lead with Matt Belloni=E2=80=99s behind-the-scenes look at Barbar=
a Broccoli and Michael G. Wilson=E2=80=99s bombshell decision to surrender =
their sacred birthright=E2=80=94creative control over James Bond=E2=80=94to=
 Amazon for a hefty, undisclosed price tag. What does the massive deal port=
end for cinema=E2=80=99s most enduring action hero, and the tech industry=
=E2=80=99s
relentless march on Hollywood?

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: John Ourand evaluates the potential hangups in NASCAR=
=E2=80=99s new media rights deals. Tara Palmeri reveals how Trump buddy Ste=
ve Witkoff leapfrogged Marco Rubio to become the administration=E2=80=99s f=
oreign policy dealmaker. And exclusively for Inner Circle members, Lauren
Sherman offers a clear-eyed analysis of the Saks Global vendor payment kerf=
uffle=E2=80=94and whether it might reshape the future of fashion retail in =
the U.S.

Meanwhile, on the pods: John Heilemann welcomes former U.S. attorney Preet =
Bharara on Impolitic to evaluate the pitched battle over Trump=E2=80=99s ag=
enda in federal courts. On Fashion People, Lauren chats with designer Emili=
a Wickstead about building a
business in London post-Brexit. On The Grill Room, Dylan Byers connects wit=
h Eriq Gardner to break down the wave of MAGA-driven lawsuits targeting Tru=
mp=E2=80=99s media enemies. And on The Powers That Be, Ourand joins Peter H=
amby to dig into the ESPN-MLB standoff.

